I got the Asian salad which was good minus the chicken that I didn’t eat cause it was dry. Looked pretty, but something I actually should have taken home to give my pup instead of wasting it. Hindsight is 20/20. The bartenders are only friendly to people they know....otherwise the synthetic dry disingenuous  “I’m here cause I have to be demeanor”  is overwhelmingly noticeable. But I still tipped because they make good drinks, and they weren’t overtly rude in their approach, more so covert stank attitude. so I  valued their one major skill set (drinks).... I’ve lived in Chicago for three years so trust me when I say I know the difference between a more introverted person who is nice versus what I’m describing here. The first time I visited the guy seemed, bothered. He gave me a bad gut feeling. From other reviews, this follows the trend that bartenders here aren’t great when it comes to service or personability , but the table servers are.  There was one guy working who actually WAS GENUINELY nice/warm the first time I ever visited, but he was not my server and was mostly serving tables, occasionally popping up behind the bar to help pass out orders. Weird. Next time I will not sit at the bar, cause I’ve sat at the bar TWICE and both times the bartender was mediocre compared to what many other venues offer.... And that’s being generous...again, ONLY cause their drink skills are bomb is this review getting 4 stars. And the nice man who picked up my coat. Such a sweetheart.

Stay away. I received an extra tip added to my bill of $50.00! None of their work phone numbers work either (online or receipt). I was unable to reach out to them, otherwise I would have avoided making this review if they had communicated. Completely unacceptable and illegal for a server (like Marcella) to add an unauthorized $50 tip.

I ate outside on the patio at this local tavern tonight. They have great outdoor seating, the service is very fast and the drinks are pretty good.  I had chicken tacos and my friend had the chicken quesadilla. The chicken in both is cubed/chunked, not shredded like one may expect, but it was still good and tasty, if a little salty.  The quesadilla was a giant portion, and the two tacos did not come with any sides but were very filling. Definitely recommend stopping by if you're in the neighborhood!

Pretty disappointed, given the high reviews. Service was awful- we got our appetizer and just had to stare at it as the waitress said she'll go get silverware, but then forgot about us. I had to get up and go inside to ask someone for it. Our check took about 20 minutes to print out, and we wanted to leave as soon as we were done. The food was decent to bad. The pork belly appetizer was really just cubes of lukewarm fat, although the sauce was very good. Fries were good but I upgraded to "THT Fries" and I wish I didn't, just tasted like weird chili on top of fries. The "THT Burger" was at times fantastic, but then I tasted lamb for some reason. Strange experience. My date didn't finish her cocktail, it wasn't that good. App, 2 meals, and 2 drinks made out to around $60 w/o tip.  Edit: changed to 3 stars due to the quick follow up from management. I might give this place a second try.

The THT is a great neighborhood bar. It tries to be a sports bar at times but doesn't do the NFL package, but otherwise does well. Good burgers and chicken sandwiches, decent appetizers, of course with great mac n cheese. Forget the desserts, they don't go with beer.
